OL,3,CSharp increase in anti-Muslim hatred
OL,4,Cin UK, particularly against women
OL,6,FIncidents recorded by the organisation
OL,7,Fincluded a Muslim woman in Islamic
OL,8,Fclothing being assaulted on a bus in
OL,9,Feast London and told "you Muslims are
OL,10,Ftroublemakers"; a written death threat
OL,11,Fto worshippers at a mosque; a woman
OL,12,Fwhose car was vandalised with a Nazi
OL,13,Fswastika; and cases of Muslim women
OL,14,Fbeing called "terrorists".
OL,16,FIman Atta, Tell Mama's director, said
OL,17,Fthe organisation was deeply concerned
OL,18,Fabout the impacts that the Israel and
OL,19,FGaza war are having on hate crimes and
OL,20,Fon social cohesion in the UK.
